For a short time Peritus is accepting applications from levels 60 -65 of all classes. This is unusual because we normally require each applicant to have a sponsor. <br>
<br>
If you want to raid 3+ times per week, you are a skilled player of your toon, you’re a mature acting person, and are willing to put the time into bringing yourself up to our level then please read further.<br>
<br>
Currently we raid Ssra Temple, BoT, Tactics, HoH, and AoW level mobs. We are past ToV and Epics for the most part. We have established raid times 4 days each week and you will be expected to attend a minimum of 60% of the raids. During your trial period you are highly encouraged to attend as many raids as possible.<br>
<br>
Most members of Peritus are level 65 with in excess of 75AA points. While we don’t expect applicants to currently be at this level they should be willing to quickly hit level 65 and begin accumulating AA points. Additionally, they will be expected to work on keys/flags so they can access the places we raid.<br>
<br>
Most members of Peritus are working adults therefore raids are held in the evenings US time or the week-ends. We do have younger players, but they are expected to act in a mature fashion.<br>
<br>
The following information was taken from our boards and addresses what Peritus is:<br>
<br>
Think of Peritus as a private club of friends, friends that like to play EQ and play it well. Anyone that doesn't meet our expectations won't last. What Peritus will soon turn out to be if I have my way is a close knit group of friends that are able to meet about 3 to 4 times per week for about 3 to 4 hours at times that can be agreed my most.<br>
<br>
- You are a mature player and play your character well (mature is not just a matter of how old you are)<br>
<br>
- You plan to make EQ your game of preference for at least the next numerous months.<br>
<br>
- You are able to dedicate 3 - 4 times per week for several hours to playing with your friends.<br>
<br>
- You keep up with the information posted on our board.<br>
<br>
- You have a good knowledge of Norrath and how to get around it, please note that ports are not the only way to get around. You carry on your character all the necessities to get you to all the zones that we frequent. (ie. SoW potions, invis potions, food and water)<br>
<br>
- You are enthusiastic but not hyper.<br>
<br>
- You are Willing to stick it out through good and bad raids (bad raid = a learning raid on a new mob)<br>
<br>
- You want to be around mature skilled players that don't need their hands held to get around.<br>
<br>
- You want to be part of a guild that makes you proud and not feel like one of your guildmates is doing immature things to embarrass you or your guild tag.<br>
<br>
- You want to be part of a guild that is extremely strong for the numbers because of how well we play together.<br>
<br>
- We will have a common goal and constantly work towards it, I don't want to feel like we're spinning our wheels.<br>
<br>
- We will be a good group of friends and be happy when our fellow guidmate gets an improvement to his/her gear.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you think you might make a good fit with Peritus please visit our boards at Peritusx.com. We encourage you to contact either Allpain or Imacabre in game with any questions. You are also welcome to seek out any of our members for groups so that you can get to know us a bit better. <br>
<br>
<br>
Allpain, Troll Warrior<br>
